A wrench is thrown across the room (don't ask why) and rotates about the z-axis running through its center of mass. The wrench has a density of [`[$density]\ g/cm^3`] and thickness of [`[$thickness]\ cm`] with dimensions [`l=[$l]\ cm`], [`w=[$w]\ cm`], and [`d=[$d]\ cm`]. Find the moment of inertia of the wrench. _(Note that the distance [`d`] is not the same as the radius)_

Center of Mass:

[`x_{CM}=`][___]{"$xCM"} [`cm`]

[`y_{CM}=`][___]{"$yCM"} [`cm`]

Moments of Inertia:

[`I_{\textrm{semicircle}}=`][___]{"$ICirc"} [`kg\cdot cm^2`]

[`I_{\textrm{rectangle}}=`][___]{"$IRod"} [`kg\cdot cm^2`]

[`I_{\textrm{total}}=`][___]{"$I"} [`kg\cdot cm^2`]

END_PGML

